The paper discusses the challenges of introducing emotion sensing technologies to instant messaging, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with detecting emotions from text-based communication. Additionally, the study involves analyzing chat logs and user feedback, which could fall under the categories of cyberpsychology (cs.CY) and social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of smartphones, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
